The '''New York State Writers Institute''' is a literary organization based at the [[University at Albany]] in [[Albany, New York]]. It sponsors a summer writer's conference,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.albany.edu/outreach/New_York_State_Writers_Institute.php |title=University at Albany - Engagement - New York State Writers Institute |publisher=Albany.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.awpwriter.org/programs_conferences/wcc_entry_view/633/new_york_state_summer_writers_institute |title=Association of Writers & Writing Programs |publisher=Awpwriter.org |date= |accessdate=2013-11-07}}</ref> visiting writers series,<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://blog.timesunion.com/localarts/new-york-state-writers-institute-announces-spring-2013-schedule/26169/ |title=New York State Writers Institute announces spring 2013 schedule - Arts Talk |publisher=Blog.timesunion.com |date=2013-01-14 |accessdate=2013-11-07}}</ref> a classic film series,<ref>http://www.albany.edu/writers-inst/webpages4/programpages/cfs.html</ref> and awards.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.pen.org/grants-and-awards/new-york-state-writers-institute-author-prize|title=New York State Writers Institute Author Prize &#124; PEN American Center|publisher=Pen.org|date=|accessdate=2013-11-07|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130807223029/http://www.pen.org/grants-and-awards/new-york-state-writers-institute-author-prize|archivedate=2013-08-07|df=}}</ref> It was founded by novelist [[William Kennedy (author)|William Kennedy]] in 1983.<ref>http://www.albany.edu/writers-inst/webpages4/institute/history.html#.V5_-vuTBRKo</ref>
